\f1\b\fs36 Splitting Documents\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_H::1><!$Scr_Ps::0>
\f1\fs28 Suppose you start out creating a single document for each chapter. Then, after your first draft, you realise that you want to break your chapters up into smaller sections, so that you can restructure more easily. No problem.\
To split the text of a document into smaller pieces:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Click into the text at the point you wish to split it apart.\
{\listtext	2.	}In the main menu, go to 
\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f2\b Documents > Split > at Selection
\f0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f1\fs28 . The document will be split in two at the cursor point.\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f2\b Documents > Split > with Selection as Title
\f0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f1\fs28  works much the same way, except you select a range of text before using it. The selected text will become the title of the newly-created document.\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl264\slmult1\sb300\sa120\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

